quran[54]{c,v,t}:
  70,19,"Indeed, man has been created impatient"
  70,20,"when evil befalls him, he becomes despondent"
  70,21,"but when blessed with good fortune, he becomes stingy"
  70,22,with the exception of those who offer the Salah (prayer)
  70,23,remain steadfast in their Salah (prayer)
  70,24,set aside a due share in their wealth
  70,25,for the beggars and the deprived
  70,26,accept the truth of the Day of Judgment
  70,27,dread the punishment of their Lord
  70,28,for none is secure from the punishment of their Lord
  70,29,and guard their private parts
  70,30,"except from their wives and those whom their right hands possess, for in their case they are not blameworthy"
  70,31,"As for those who seek to go beyond this, they are transgressors"
  70,32,Those who keep their trusts and honor their promises
  70,33,who stand firm in their testimonies
  70,34,and strictly guard their Salah (prayers)
  70,35,It is they who shall live with honor in paradise
  70,36,What is the matter with the disbelievers that they are rushing towards you
  70,37,"from the right and from the left, in groups"
  70,38,Are they each seeking to enter the garden of bliss
  70,39,"By no means! Surely, We have created them out of that what they (unbelievers) know"
  70,40,"But nay! I swear by the Lord of the easts and the wests, that We have the power"
  70,41,"to destroy them and replace them with others better than them, and nothing can hinder Us from doing so"
  70,42,"Therefore, leave them to plunge in vain talk and blunder about until they face that Day of theirs which they are being promised"
  70,43,"The Day when they shall rush forward from their graves, as if they were racing towards a goal, with downcast eyes and countenances distorted with shame"
  70,44,"Such will be the Day, which they are being promised"
  71,1,"We sent Noah to his people, saying: \"Give warning to your people before there comes to them a painful punishment"
  71,2,"He said: \"O my People! I am sent towards you as a plain Warner"
  71,3,"Worship Allah, fear Him and obey me"
  71,4,"If you will do so, He will forgive you your sins and give you respite for an appointed term. The fact is that when the term given by Allah arrives, it cannot be deferred. If you could understand"
  71,5,"After exhausting all his efforts Noah said: \"O Lord! I have pleaded with my people night and day"
  71,6,but my plea has only added to their aversion
  71,7,"Each time I called on them to seek Your pardon, they thrust their fingers in their ears and drew their cloaks over their heads, persisting in sin and puffing themselves up with insolent pride"
  71,8,I have called them aloud
  71,9,appealed them openly in public and secretly in private
  71,10,"saying: \"Seek forgiveness of your Lord, He is ever ready to forgive you"
  71,11,He will send abundant rain for you from heaven
  71,12,"help you with wealth and sons, and provide you with gardens and the flowing rivers"
  71,13,What is the matter with you that you do not regard the greatness of Allah
  71,14,when He has created you in gradual stages
  71,15,Can you not see how Allah created the seven heavens one above the other
  71,16,placing in them the moon as a light and the sun as a glorious lamp
  71,17,Allah has caused you to grow as a growth from the earth
  71,18,He will return you to the same earth and then raise you back to life again on the Day of Resurrection
  71,19,Allah has made the earth for you as a wide expanse
  71,20,so that you may walk in its spacious paths
  71,21,"Finally, Noah submitted: \"O Lord! My people have disobeyed me, and followed those chiefs whose wealth and children have added to them nothing but loss"
  71,22,They have devised an outrageous plot
  71,23,"and said to each other: 'Do not leave your gods; especially Wadd, Suwa, Yaghus, Yauq and Nasr (the names of their idols)"
  71,24,"They have already misled many, so O Lord, do not increase the wrongdoers in anything but deviation"
  71,25,Because of their wrong doings they were drowned in the great flood and made to enter the fire. They found no one besides Allah to help them
  71,26,"As Noah had prayed: \"O Lord! Do not leave a single unbeliever on the surface of the earth"
  71,27,"For if You spare any of them, they will mislead your servants and beget none but wicked unbelievers"
  71,28,"O Lord! Forgive me, my parents and every true believer who seeks refuge in my house, and all believing men and believing women. As to the wrongdoers, grant them increase in nothing but destruction"